Diagnosis:
Small (<
3 mm
), slender, smooth, translucent, posterium often longer than trunk; sclerites adpressed; trunk sclerites short (to 
120 µm
), thin (to 
5 µm
), curved, sausage-shaped, blade as a small, sharp nipple; sclerites fringing knob in single row, extending beyond knob; 2 rows oral shield sclerites indistinct.
